  <data name="Usage_Title" xml:space="preserve"><value>How to Use</value></data>
  <data name="Usage_Text" xml:space="preserve"><value>Nanum CSV Viewer — Quick Guide

[Open]
• File ▸ Open (Ctrl+O) opens .csv / .txt as well as Excel (.xlsx/.xls), SAS (.sas7bdat), and SPSS (.sav).
• The first page appears instantly; the rest is indexed in the background (progress bar at the bottom). You can scroll while indexing.
• Multi-sheet Excel workbooks switch via the sheet tabs at the bottom.
• For SPSS/SAS, View ▸ Show Field Labels swaps codes and names for value labels and variable labels.
• SPSS/SAS declared types (currency, percent, date, categorical, ordinal…) are matched automatically; currency and percent columns show their symbols.

[Encoding]
• Auto-detected (UTF-8 / UTF-8 BOM / CP949·EUC-KR). If wrong, click the encoding widget at the right of the status bar, or use View ▸ Encoding. No re-indexing needed.

[Find]
• Type in the Find box and press Enter, or F3, to jump to the next match (case-insensitive, wraps around).

[Filter]
• Use the funnel icon on a header for type-aware filters: range for numbers/time, checkboxes for categories/booleans, text predicates (contains/regex/list/blank) for strings/identifiers.
• Active conditions appear as chips above the grid — remove with ✕, click to edit, toggle ALL (AND) / ANY (OR).
• Filter by Cell (Ctrl+B) and the Advanced expression filter (AND/OR/parentheses). Clear removes all.

[Sort]
• Click a column header to sort (click again to toggle direction).
• Shift+Click headers to sort by multiple columns (priority shown on each header).
• Equal values keep their original order (stable sort). Clear Sort restores file order.

[Analysis]
• Facets panel (F6): see per-column distributions (histogram / top values) and click a bar to filter instantly (cross-filtering).
• Analyze / Statistics / Pivot menus: distributions, correlation, tests, group aggregation, pivot table/chart. Export: CSV/Markdown/JSON/HTML.

[Detail Panel]
• Toggle with the Details button or F4. Shows every column of the selected row as name + value — handy for cells with line breaks.

[Status Light]
• The colored dot at the right end of the status bar: ⚪ Idle · 🟡 Loading · 🟠 Busy · 🟢 Ready.

[Theme]
• Use the theme toggle at the right of the toolbar to switch light/dark.

[Shortcuts]
Ctrl+O Open · Ctrl+Q Quit · Ctrl+F Find · F3 Find Next · Ctrl+G Go to Row
Ctrl+B Filter by Cell · Ctrl+Shift+L Clear Filter · Ctrl+Shift+S Clear Sort
F4 Detail Panel · F6 Facets Panel · F1 This help</value></data>
